    - m_Type: 0
      Title:
        m_Untranslated: Fixing the DebugHitInfo Function Call
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: "You should notice that once an enemy has been near the player,
          that enemy will keep the red cross even after leaving the radius of the
          player. If you play for long enough, the red crosses on these enemies will
          also disappear (at the same time that you go near another enemy or wall).
          \r\nThe reason for this is that the <c>collidersNearMe</c> array is being
          updated every frame to contain the new information about what colliders
          are near the player, but it is not being cleared at the start of every
          frame. <b>You can see this for yourself by running the game and watching
          the contents of the public array in the inspector</b>.\nThe <c>NonAlloc</c>
          function only adds items to the start of the array\u2014it stops once it
          has finished placing items in the array, rather than going on to clear
          the end of the array. If you have done any C programming, you may have
          come across this sort of functionality when working with arrays.\r\nTo
          fix this problem, the <c>RaycastUtils.DebugHitInfo</c> function has an
          overloaded version (aka second version) which takes this special integer
          variable as a parameter. "
